Well he isn't wrong as good eating habits established early will indeed last but that said? Do not force it because it can and will leave a negative impact in the subconscious. Which can lead to them never truly liking the food in the future. So establish the habits but making your kid sit at the table for a hour just to eat lettuce won't help!


Oh.. and guy science has now proven that what you eat affects the bacteria in your stomach. Which can send signals to your brain for you to eat more of X food to keep it alive. So once you start eating bad this is another reason it is hard to get back in track. They have poop transplants now that can help with this but really better habits started young are a much better call.
